description: Use app-styled confirmation modals instead of browser alerts or wire:confirm
alwaysApply: true
---

# Confirmation UI

- Never use browser-native `alert()`, `confirm()`, or `prompt()` in this project.
- Never introduce `wire:confirm` for destructive or high-impact actions.
- Use a proper app-styled modal or equivalent in-product confirmation flow instead.
- Confirmation copy should explain what will happen and what the user is confirming.

## Examples

### Avoid

```blade
<button wire:click="deleteSite" wire:confirm="Delete this site?">
    Delete
</button>
```

```javascript
if (confirm('Delete this site?')) {
  destroySite()
}
```

### Prefer

```blade
<button type="button" wire:click="openDeleteSiteModal">
    Delete
</button>

<x-modal name="delete-site-confirmation">
    <p>Delete this site from Dply?</p>
    <x-danger-button wire:click="deleteSite">Delete site</x-danger-button>
</x-modal>
```
